Defendant Waldo Medina-Guzman in court with attorney Daniel E Meylink.  James C. Griffin appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Deputy court clerk ccp.
Case set for sentencing hearing. Parties are prepared to proceed. State placed negotiations on the record. Statements made as to sentencing. Additional statements made by Jose G-M. with the assistance of sworn interpreter Brenda Bartholomew. Exhibits 1 & 2 received. 

As to COUNT 1 as AMENDED-
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 5 YEARS, with credit for 3 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 3 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 2 YEARS.  

Defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program. The defendant is NOT eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.

Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on probation for 4 YEARS. 

The following conditions of probation will be conditions of extended supervision if revoked:
1) Court ordered 180 days of condition time in the House of Correction, IMPOSED BUT STAYED to be used at the discretion of the agent. Release privileges to be determined at the discretion of the agent. Defendant to serve 14 days of the condition time FORTHWITH. During the 14 days, the defendant may have release for school upon providing proof to the House of Correction and may participate in programming at the House. 
2) Restitution set at ZERO;
3) Provide DNA sample and pay DNA surcharge;
4) Absolutely no driving for 6 months;
5) AODA assessment and comply with recommended treatment;
6) Maintain absolute sobriety from all illegal drugs and alcohol;
7) Random urine screens;
8) Anger management classes;
9) Pay all costs, fees and surcharges during period of probation;
10) Attend a cognitive thinking program;
11) No contact with the victim or any Class B licensed tavern;
12) Maintain employment of at least 30 hours per week;

Court ordered cash bail on deposit to apply. Any remaining bail on deposit to be returned to poster.

Appellate rights notice given to the defendant. 
Filed;
